---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Custom styles — react-data-table-component">
  <h1>Custom styles</h1>

  <p>
    The <code>customStyles</code> prop accepts a <code>TableStyles</code> object.
    Each key targets a specific part of the table and accepts a <code>style</code> property
    with standard <code>React.CSSProperties</code> values.
  </p>

  <h2>Basic example</h2>

  <pre><code>{`import DataTable, { type TableStyles } from 'react-data-table-component';

const customStyles: TableStyles = {
  headRow: {
    style: {
      backgroundColor: '#f0f4ff',
      fontWeight: 700,
    },
  },
  rows: {
    style: {
      fontSize: '14px',
    },
    selectedHighlightStyle: {
      backgroundColor: '#e0eaff',
    },
  },
  cells: {
    style: {
      paddingLeft: '16px',
      paddingRight: '16px',
    },
  },
};

<DataTable columns={columns} data={data} customStyles={customStyles} />`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Available style targets</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Key</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>table</code></td><td>The root <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> wrapping the table</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>tableWrapper</code></td><td>Inner wrapper for overflow handling</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>responsiveWrapper</code></td><td>Horizontal scroll container</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>header</code></td><td>Title bar above the table</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>subHeader</code></td><td>Sub-header area (search, actions)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>head</code></td><td>Column header area</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>headRow</code></td><td>Column header row</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>headCells</code></td><td>Column header cells</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>contextMenu</code></td><td>Context menu (shown when rows are selected)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>cells</code></td><td>Body cells</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>rows</code></td><td>Body rows (includes <code>selectedHighlightStyle</code>)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>expanderRow</code></td><td>Expanded row container</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>expanderCell</code></td><td>Expander toggle cell</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>expanderButton</code></td><td>Expand/collapse button icon</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>pagination</code></td><td>Pagination bar</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>noData</code></td><td>Empty-state container</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>progress</code></td><td>Loading state container</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Row-level styles</h2>

  <p>
    For conditional row styling, use <code>conditionalRowStyles</code> instead of
    <code>customStyles</code>. It accepts a <code>when</code> predicate and style object:
  </p>

  <pre><code>{`<DataTable
  columns={columns}
  data={data}
  conditionalRowStyles={[
    {
      when: row => row.salary > 100000,
      style: { backgroundColor: '#fff9e6' },
    },
    {
      when: row => row.active === false,
      style: { opacity: 0.5 },
    },
  ]}
/>`}</code></pre>

  <h2>CSS custom properties</h2>

  <p>
    For theming that affects the entire table, prefer CSS custom properties via
    <code>createTheme</code> or by overriding variables directly. See the{' '}
    <a href="/docs/themes">Themes</a> page.
  </p>

  <h2>Migrating from v7</h2>

  <p>
    In v7, <code>customStyles</code> values accepted <code>CSSObject</code> from styled-components.
    In v8, they accept <code>React.CSSProperties</code>. The practical difference:
    pseudo-selectors like <code>&:hover</code> are not valid CSS properties.
    Use <code>conditionalRowStyles</code> or CSS classes for hover and focus states.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
